<p>I am working on designing zero-knowledge proofs of reserves for different cryptocurrencies. I designed Revelio+, an efficient proof of reserves for <a href="https://github.com/mimblewimble/">MimbleWimble</a> based cryptocurrencies. MimbleWimble has outputs instead of addresses to store coins. Using our protocol, an exchange proves in zero-knowledge that it owns particular outputs from the set of unspent outputs on the blockchain preserving privacy of outputs owned by an exchange. Further, it also helps detect collusion between exchanges when they try to share an output in their respective proofs of reserves.</p>

<p>A typical Revelio+ proof would be of the form
